1
00:00:06,690 --> 00:00:08,300
Just hear me out!

2
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:09,610
Listen to me for once, will you?

3
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:11,770
Let me explain why I'm doing this.

4
00:00:11,770 --> 00:00:13,540
Something horrible is going on!

5
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,580
Be quiet!

6
00:00:15,580 --> 00:00:17,650
Ouch...

7
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:19,700
Come on...

8
00:00:23,390 --> 00:00:25,630
Guk-Hee, are you okay?

9
00:00:25,630 --> 00:00:27,530
Who is he?

10
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:28,520
You and your friends...

11
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:30,680
...always get stuck with scoundrels
like him whenever you go.

12
00:00:30,690 --> 00:00:33,790
I got a phone call to come
in for the missing girl.

13
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:38,540
Honey, are you okay?

14
00:00:38,540 --> 00:00:40,550
Honey?

15
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:44,380
You have a husband?

16
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:46,470
Who are you?

17
00:00:47,510 --> 00:00:49,450
Oh...

18
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:52,500
I'm Guk-Hee's friend.

19
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,390
Friend?

20
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,400
What the heck?

21
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:59,310
Whose friend? Since when?

22
00:00:59,310 --> 00:01:00,480
Honey, he's not a friend.

23
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:01,750
I don't have friends.

24
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:05,570
I met him at the beach,
but there's nothing between us.

25
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:07,550
You don't know anything!
Why did you punch him?

26
00:01:07,550 --> 00:01:10,340
Tell him that you're sorry!

27
00:01:10,340 --> 00:01:12,660
You were so rude to her.

28
00:01:12,660 --> 00:01:15,330
I never would've guessed
that you're her husband.

29
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:18,300
What? Why, I ought to...

30
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:20,530
Guk-Hee! They want you inside!

31
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:23,490
Honey, are you okay?

32
00:01:23,490 --> 00:01:24,490
Let me help you get up.

33
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:25,420
Don't get mad, Honey.

34
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,510
Stay calm, will you?

35
00:01:27,510 --> 00:01:29,630
Apologize! Tell him that you're sorry.

36
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,500
I'm sorry!

37
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:33,670
Do it sincerely!

38
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:35,470
Forget it!

39
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:40,320
If I ever see you again,
you're going to get it!

40
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,570
Got that?

41
00:01:41,570 --> 00:01:43,690
You tiny little prick!

42
00:01:43,690 --> 00:01:44,750
Let go!

43
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:50,710
Honey! Honey...

44
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:53,770
Honey...

45
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:58,330
Guk-Hee! Come inside...

46
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:11,300
- Episode 3 -
Why didn't you call earlier?

47
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:15,590
The officers and the neighbors
were all worried about you.

48
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:23,470
Someone even accused me.

49
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:28,400
Anyways, I'm glad you're safe.

50
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,480
I love you.

51
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,400
It's my wife.

52
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,660
- Lee Yun-Shil?
- Yes.

53
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:39,420
I'm calling from the police station.

54
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:43,450
I have a few questions to ask
about your missing case.

55
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,390
You're Lee Yun-Shil, right?

56
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:51,340
Can I get your resident
ID number and your address?

57
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:54,460
Good, thank you.

58
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:57,410
Bye. Thank you for your cooperation.

59
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:00,590
I've always been an honest man.

60
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,780
Don't treat me like a criminal.

61
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:12,370
I'll go home and think hard about how you should be reprimanded for this.

62
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,770
Bye.

63
00:03:27,730 --> 00:03:29,630
Honey, it's me.

64
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:31,600
Are you home?

65
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:35,570
Hello? Hello? Hello?

66
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,790
You're not in college, right?

67
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:41,510
Why did you lie to me?

68
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:46,610
Huh? I'm sorry,
but I have to go home.

69
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:51,310
Hey! Gyung Guk-Hee!

70
00:03:53,510 --> 00:03:56,520
I'm sorry I did that.

71
00:03:56,520 --> 00:04:00,690
Still, you shouldn't have punched
him without checking who he is.

72
00:04:01,510 --> 00:04:05,310
I'm really sorry for lying, though.

73
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,720
Honey!

74
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:23,610
Get out!

75
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,300
Get out!

76
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:25,660
I'm sorry.

77
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:28,310
Get out! Now!

78
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:30,520
Honey! Honey!

79
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:50,660
Open the door.

80
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:52,480
This isn't right.

81
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,420
Eun-Suk! Ki-Suk!

82
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:57,310
Honey! Honey!

83
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:03,370
Honey! You only need milk
from the store, right?

84
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:04,440
Okay.

85
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:14,570
Honey! I'm sorry!

86
00:05:14,570 --> 00:05:17,400
Eun-Suk! Ki-Suk!
Can you hear me?

87
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,760
Ki-Suk! Eun-Suk!

88
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:27,310
Don't open the door
without my permission.

89
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:29,460
Go to your room.

90
00:05:32,410 --> 00:05:35,390
Honey! This isn't right!

91
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:49,540
Honey, please open the door.

92
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:21,400
Why, I ought to...

93
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:26,740
Why, I ought to...

94
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:30,380
I'm Myung-Hoon.

95
00:06:30,380 --> 00:06:32,400
Is Eun-Suk home?

96
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,580
Hey! It's Myung-Hoon!

97
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:36,660
Is he your friend?

98
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:40,570
I'm here to return Eun-Suk's book!

99
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,480
He brought your book.

100
00:06:45,730 --> 00:06:47,480
Hold on.

101
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:53,690
Mom!

102
00:06:54,630 --> 00:07:00,310
I helped you because you helped me
get my cat out of the gutter.

103
00:07:00,310 --> 00:07:02,550
Don't ask me for favors
like this anymore!

104
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:07,440
I won't. Thanks, Myung-Hoon.

105
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,700
Goodnight, Eun-Suk.

106
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,650
Bye.

107
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:11,420
Bye.

108
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:24,600
I know that you're angry, but you shouldn't kick me out like this.

109
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,640
Where do you expect me
to go this late at night?

110
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,700
You're going too far.

111
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:39,350
The four of us went to the beach,
but one disappeared.

112
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:41,560
It was crazy, and I couldn't
even tell you about it.

113
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,730
I was scared to death.

114
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:44,770
Anyways, we got in touch with her.

115
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:46,310
She's okay.

116
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:47,770
It's all over now.

117
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:53,540
I think that man's so weird.

118
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:55,310
I can't believe he punched you.

119
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,510
Since you're the better man,
just let him go.

120
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:59,550
I'll tell him off, although I doubt
I'll ever see him again.

121
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:03,550
Are you okay?

122
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:05,390
Stop it!

123
00:08:06,770 --> 00:08:08,370
What are we going to do?

124
00:08:08,370 --> 00:08:10,500
Stop it!

125
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,640
Leave me alone!

126
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,400
Honey! Kids!

127
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,540
Wake up! Let's eat.

128
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:57,360
Honey...I'll pick out your tie.

129
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:01,770
You look great!

130
00:09:03,650 --> 00:09:06,500
Do you want that instead?

131
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,690
Well, you look good in anything.

132
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:11,310
People will think you're
Eun-Suk's uncle...

133
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:13,680
...if you wear that for Eun-Suk's camp.

134
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:19,670
Honey, I know I picked this out,
but doesn't it look really good?

135
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:24,570
You can't tell that it's fake!

136
00:09:25,650 --> 00:09:27,730
This knockoff looks like the real thing.

137
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,720
Let's have breakfast.

138
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:37,480
I made your favorite seaweed soup
and stir-fried potatoes.

139
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:40,320
Seaweed soup and stir-fried potatoes?

140
00:09:40,610 --> 00:09:44,720
Do you think you can be
a good wife by good cooking?

141
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:51,630
I'm worn out and don't have
anything to look forward to in life.

142
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:56,770
I'm about to go postal because I can never get any rest from work or home!

143
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,620
I don't need stir-fried potatoes.

144
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:01,490
Just don't drive me crazy!

145
00:10:01,490 --> 00:10:05,370
Who knows what I'll do
if you stoop any lower?

146
00:10:05,370 --> 00:10:06,680
Understand?

147
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:14,710
Su-Duk!

148
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:23,650
You dodged!

149
00:10:27,330 --> 00:10:29,310
Su-Duk will get a time-out.

150
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,600
I'll sit here for my time-out.

151
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,610
I'll never go to the police
station again, I promise!

152
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:41,480
What a shame!

153
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,590
Not only those women
didn't come home for the night...

154
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:47,440
...they had to go to the police station.

155
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:51,420
The other people will think
we're just like them.

156
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:54,530
I wonder why the tenants
won't stop making trouble.

157
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:58,530
Yes, but our biggest problem
is the divorcee!

158
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:02,680
I'll tell the homeowners not to give
rent to families with problems.

159
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,760
Good idea!

160
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:07,330
They'll ruin our neighborhood!

161
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:10,650
Keep an eye on your husband.

162
00:11:10,650 --> 00:11:13,400
Make sure he doesn't
get bitten by a crazy dog.

163
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,450
Eun-Suk!

164
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,370
What happened to your face?

165
00:11:26,370 --> 00:11:27,580
Did you fight with your friend?

166
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:33,510
Myung-Hoon's mom said that I can't
run for class president because of you!

167
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:35,790
Because of me?

168
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:38,640
Because you went to the police station!

169
00:11:41,690 --> 00:11:43,640
Myung-Hoon's mom!

170
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:49,300
Is it true that Eun-Suk
can't run for class president?

171
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,510
It's a decision made by the PTA.

172
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:53,610
Let me explain.

173
00:11:53,610 --> 00:11:57,470
The reason why I went to the police station is not because I broke the law.

174
00:11:57,470 --> 00:12:00,720
Besides, Eun-Suk shouldn't be
punished for what I've done.

175
00:12:00,730 --> 00:12:02,450
Let's go.

176
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,410
Hello?

177
00:12:37,330 --> 00:12:38,510
Suk-Doo?

178
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,380
Park Suk-Doo?

179
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:44,510
Dead? Who's dead?

180
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,790
A dead body?

181
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:50,320
She's dead?

182
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:55,760
Oh, my Gosh...

183
00:12:59,310 --> 00:13:04,600
They found her body about 3km
away from the beach we were in.

184
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:08,700
Oh, no...

185
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:10,660
This is a dream, right?

186
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,700
Honey!

187
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,660
Mom...

188
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:18,450
We need the kids to stay outside.

189
00:13:18,450 --> 00:13:19,680
This can be too much
for them to handle.

190
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:21,380
I'll take them outside.

191
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:23,600
Kids, come with me.

192
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:27,660
Honey!

193
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:32,490
How can this happen?

194
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:35,740
Honey...

195
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:42,360
Ms. Lee Yun-Shil doesn't have any contacts on her paternal family.

196
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:45,570
She's an orphan.

197
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:49,340
I'm the only family she has.

198
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:51,410
Honey...

199
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,700
You were legally married 4 years ago.

200
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,390
What about the kids?

201
00:14:02,690 --> 00:14:05,680
They're from my previous marriage.

202
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:12,780
I was always worried about her
because she's very emotional...

203
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:18,620
...but I never imagined
she'd really do this...

204
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:20,530
What do you mean?

205
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:28,350
She tried to commit suicide
in the past out of depression.

206
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:34,580
Suicide? Suicide?

207
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:36,390
Don't mind them.

208
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:39,690
They don't know my wife very well.

209
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:41,650
They're just neighbors.

210
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:47,690
Excuse me.

211
00:14:55,530 --> 00:14:57,770
This is so dirty...

212
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:05,500
How can you be so nonchalant
all of a sudden when your wife's dead?

213
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,510
Aren't you sad?

214
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:09,650
Are you sure you didn't kill her?

215
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:14,570
What? How can you say that?

216
00:15:15,350 --> 00:15:16,700
Calm down.

217
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:20,790
We can't be sure yet, so calm down.

218
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:23,530
Yun-Shil needs someone on her side.

219
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:26,440
Why does she need you on her side?

220
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,670
I'm her husband!

221
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,410
Get out.

222
00:15:30,410 --> 00:15:31,520
Get out, please.

223
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:35,640
Get out! Get out!

224
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:39,670
No! You're acting weird!

225
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,500
Why, I ought to...

226
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:46,330
You're acting weird.

227
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:47,790
Get out of my way!

228
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:53,490
Did you just hit Su-Duk? Why?

229
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:55,370
Why I ought to...

230
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:56,640
Stop it!

231
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:05,470
What are you guys doing?

232
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:14,460
Do you think the white pants killed her?

233
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:18,340
Does that mean I was with a murderer?

234
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:20,560
Let's tell the police.

235
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,340
What are we going to tell them?

236
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:25,520
About the so-called phone call
with Yun-Shil, the bloody scarf...

237
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:26,710
...and that he was cheating on her.

238
00:16:26,710 --> 00:16:28,700
The policemen here don't know that.

239
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:34,360
To be honest with you,
I won't want to take a part in this.

240
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:37,400
It's scary, and I already
have enough problems as it is.

241
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,750
I'm sure the police will help her.

242
00:16:42,350 --> 00:16:46,570
Uh...the same goes for Su-Duk.

243
00:16:46,570 --> 00:16:50,620
Su-Duk is just a housewife.

244
00:16:50,620 --> 00:16:54,580
Su-Duk's job is to cook and
do the laundry. That's it.

245
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:00,350
Oh, it's time to make dinner.

246
00:17:00,350 --> 00:17:02,370
Su-Duk needs to go and make dinner.

247
00:17:04,430 --> 00:17:06,480
I better go before there's traffic.

248
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:18,390
I wish I had a friend like you.

249
00:17:22,410 --> 00:17:22,780
Cheer up.

250
00:17:22,780 --> 00:17:24,790
Where there's a will, there's a way.

251
00:17:24,790 --> 00:17:29,670
If you need help,
I'll help you...as a friend.

252
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,600
I'm scared...

253
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:29,430
Su-Duk...

254
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:31,750
Oh, my gosh!

255
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:35,340
I'm sorry, Yun-Shil!

256
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:06,700
Hello?

257
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,310
Are you sleeping?

258
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,310
No.

259
00:19:14,350 --> 00:19:15,420
Hold on.

260
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,600
Hello?

261
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,390
Are you sleeping?

262
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:27,420
I saw a ghost.

263
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:28,650
I'm scared.

264
00:19:28,650 --> 00:19:31,420
Su-Duk can't sleep tonight.

265
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,570
I tried to let it slide, but I can't.

266
00:19:33,570 --> 00:19:37,360
Now that I want to do something
about it, there's nothing I can do!

267
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,420
I hate it!

268
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,410
We need more information.

269
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,500
What should we do?

270
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:45,590
I don't know.

271
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:48,310
We're not the police or detectives.

272
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:50,620
